ATMOSphere §GS-1: drop mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f sentinel from rkmpp configure check

The RK3588 device's Rockchip MPP (rockchip_mpp) ABI predates the
mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f symbol that upstream FFmpeg added to the rkmpp
require_pkg_config sentinel list. The symbol is a configure-only
gatekeeper — it is NOT referenced anywhere in the rkmpp decoder source
(grep mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f libavcodec/rkmppdec.c == 0). On a device
whose libmpp exports mpp_create but not mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f, the
upstream sentinel makes ./configure REJECT --enable-rkmpp, silently
disabling HW HEVC/H.264/VP9 decode on RK3588.

Fix: remove mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f from the sentinel symbol list,
keeping mpp_create (which the device DOES export). rkmpp HW decode then
configures and links correctly against the device MPP ABI.

This patch is applied by buildscripts/scripts/ffmpeg.sh AFTER the FFmpeg
source is fetched (git clone in include/download-deps.sh) and BEFORE
./configure runs, because deps/ffmpeg is gitignored + re-fetched on
clean builds — an on-disk-only edit would be lost.

Apply: git -C deps/ffmpeg apply -p1 < <this-file>   (idempotent guard in ffmpeg.sh)
Target: FFmpeg n8.0.1 (depinfo.sh v_ci_ffmpeg=n8.0.1); also applies to n8.2-dev.

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 8f9fb04115..c6f1ba3409 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -7508,7 +7508,8 @@ enabled openssl           && { { check_pkg_config openssl "openssl >= 3.0.0" ope
                                check_lib openssl openssl/ssl.h DTLS_get_data_mtu -lssl -lcrypto -lws2_32 -lgdi32 ||
                                die "ERROR: openssl (>= 1.1.1) not found"; }
 enabled pocketsphinx      && require_pkg_config pocketsphinx pocketsphinx pocketsphinx/pocketsphinx.h ps_init
-enabled rkmpp             && { require_pkg_config rkmpp "rockchip_mpp >= 1.3.8" "rockchip/rk_mpi.h rockchip/mpp_buffer.h" "mpp_create mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f" &&
+# ATMOSphere §GS-1: device MPP ABI predates the mpp_buffer_sync_begin_f sentinel; symbol unused by rkmppdec.c (grep=0). Keep mpp_create only.
+enabled rkmpp             && { require_pkg_config rkmpp "rockchip_mpp >= 1.3.8" "rockchip/rk_mpi.h rockchip/mpp_buffer.h" "mpp_create" &&
                                { enabled libdrm ||
                                  die "ERROR: rkmpp requires --enable-libdrm"; }
                              }
